    <fr:title text="Relative Booleanisation is Boolean iff it has Stone fibres">Relative Booleanisation is Boolean iff it has Stone fibres</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D \to  E]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>-algebra. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda _DE]]></fr:tex> be the pushout of this map along the Booleanisation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D \to  \lambda  D]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda _DE]]></fr:tex> is Boolean iff for the corresponding map on spectra <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : \operatorname {Spec} E \to  \operatorname {Spec} D]]></fr:tex>, for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  \operatorname {Spec} D]]></fr:tex> the fibre <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}(x)]]></fr:tex> is a Stone space.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>18</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  Notice that we have the following pullback,
  
  <html:figure><fr:resource hash="6bbf865e00f2580d12792cffba763f2a"><fr:resource-content><html:img src="/6bbf865e00f2580d12792cffba763f2a.svg" /></fr:resource-content><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="preamble"><![CDATA[\usepackage {tikz-cd}\usepackage {quiver}]]></fr:resource-source><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="body"><![CDATA[
  \begin {tikzcd}
    {\mathrm {Spec}\,\lambda _DE} & {\mathrm {Spec}\,\lambda  D} \\
    {\mathrm {Spec}\,E} & {\mathrm {Spec}\,D}
    \arrow [from=1-1, to=1-2]
    \arrow [from=1-1, to=2-1]
    \arrow ["\lrcorner "{anchor=center, pos=0.125}, draw=none, from=1-1, to=2-2]
    \arrow [from=1-2, to=2-2]
    \arrow ["f"', from=2-1, to=2-2]
  \end {tikzcd}
  ]]></fr:resource-source></fr:resource></html:figure>

  By <fr:link href="/idem-comm-E7E2/" title="Boolean algebras only have maximal ideals" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-E7E2/" display-uri="idem-comm-E7E2" type="local">Remark <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-E7E2/" display-uri="idem-comm-E7E2" /></fr:link>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda _DE]]></fr:tex> is Boolean iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}\lambda _DE]]></fr:tex> is discrete. Since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}\lambda  D \to  \operatorname {Spec} D]]></fr:tex> is bijective on points, so is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}\lambda _DE \to  \operatorname {Spec} E]]></fr:tex>. Now for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\le  y\in \operatorname {Spec} E]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \le  y]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}\lambda _DE]]></fr:tex> iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[fx = fy]]></fr:tex> since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}\lambda  D]]></fr:tex> is discrete. It follows that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}\lambda _DE]]></fr:tex> is discrete iff the fibres of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> are discrete, which makes them Stone spaces since they are spectral.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
